---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const lang = "en";
---

<Layout
  title="Our actions - Pachatopia"
  description="Regenerating the Earth and building a sustainable future: natural reserves, regenerative agriculture, local production, sustainable aquaculture, and collective participation."
  lang={lang}
>
  <Header lang={lang} />
  <main>
    <!-- Hero Banner -->
    <section class="relative text-white py-24 md:py-32 overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute inset-0">
        <img src="/images/farm-hero.jpg" alt="Our actions" class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover" aria-hidden="true" />
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-primary/80"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="container mx-auto px-6 text-center relative z-10 max-w-4xl">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-heading font-bold mb-6">Our actions</h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-white/90">Regenerating the Earth and building a sustainable future</p>
      </div>
      <svg class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-full" viewBox="0 0 1440 80" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" preserveAspectRatio="none">
        <path d="M0 40C240 80 480 0 720 40C960 80 1200 0 1440 40V80H0V40Z" fill="white"/>
      </svg>
    </section>

    <!-- Intro -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">At Pachatopia, we develop concrete initiatives to restore ecosystems, support local communities, and promote a way of life that respects the living world. Our actions revolve around several complementary areas.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Action Articles -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-cream">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 space-y-14">
        <article>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-4">🌳 Creating natural reserves</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Protecting biodiversity is at the heart of our commitment. We work to create natural reserves in order to preserve forests, local wildlife, and plant life. These spaces also contribute to protecting freshwater sources and maintaining ecological balance.</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">By restoring and protecting these ecosystems, we also participate in natural carbon capture, thus contributing to the fight against climate change. Our ambition is to transform these lands into biodiversity refuges and learning spaces for future generations.</p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-4">🌱 Developing regenerative agriculture</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">We are gradually developing an agricultural model inspired by natural ecosystems. Our goal is to implement diversified agroforestry systems where crops coexist with trees and biodiversity.</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">This model helps improve soil fertility, reduce the use of chemical inputs, promote biodiversity, and produce higher-quality food.</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">We move forward in this transition step by step, learning directly in the field and drawing inspiration from traditional farming practices and agroecological knowledge.</p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-4">☕ Enhancing local production</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">We seek to maximize the value of resources produced on the territory. Coffee is currently one of our main products. We aim to gradually develop local roasting, in order to create a more autonomous and sustainable regional supply chain.</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">We also explore different ways to add value to agricultural by-products: processing coffee pulp, fermentation and production of natural fertilizers, and using agricultural waste to produce energy.</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">The goal is to develop a circular economy, where every resource is used intelligently and sustainably.</p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-4">🐟 Developing sustainable aquaculture</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">The San Carlos region is rich in water resources and has significant potential for fish production. We aim to develop more sustainable aquaculture systems capable of producing quality food while limiting environmental impact.</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">By valorizing organic waste and integrating different production systems, we seek to transform these practices into more ecological and efficient models.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Participate -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-6">🤝 Join the Pachatopia adventure</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Pachatopia is a collective project. Everyone can contribute to this initiative:</p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">• by supporting tree planting</p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">• by discovering our coffee</p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">• by coming to participate in field activities</p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">• or by financially supporting our actions.</p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">Together, we can regenerate the Earth and build a more harmonious future.</p>
        <a href="/en/comment-participer/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-8 py-3 bg-golden text-primary font-semibold rounded-full hover:bg-golden-dark transition-colors">Support Pachatopia</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer lang={lang} />
</Layout>
